To compile libexif for Windows or Mac OS X follow the steps below, note that
for Linux the libexif-dev package should be installed instead.

Mac OS X:
- Make sure XCode is installed and start a terminal.

- Extract the libexif sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- Configure libexif using:
  ./configure --enable-static

- Run make and copy the libexif.a file to ext/exif/bin.macx.

Windows:
- Make sure MinGW and MSYS are installed and start a MinGW bash shell.

- Extract the libexif sources somewhere and cd into the source directory.

- Configure libexif using:
  ./configure --enable-static

- In the mingw installation directory; copy and rename mingw32-make.exe
  into make.exe.
  
- Run make and copy the libexif.a file to ext/exif/bin.win32.

- In the mingw installation directory; remove make.exe again.
